jdrasil.algorithms.exact

Class SATDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • jdrasil.algorithms.exact.SATDecomposer<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.concurrent.Callable<TreeDecomposition<T>>, TreeDecomposer<T>

    public class SATDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements TreeDecomposer<T>, java.io.Serializable
    This TreeDecomposer computes a tree-decomposition using the base encoding @see BaseEncoder.java. The class is generic in the sence, that as initial parameter a SATSolver object is expected. A call of @see call() will then envoce JNI and run the provides SATSolver with a constructed formula. This may lead to multiple calls.
    See Also:
